20.) Can I specify fractional weight values such as 670 or 973 for font weight?
--> Yes you can, but CSS will round off to the nearest actual weight.

21.) What is the hierarchy that is being followed when it comes to style sheets?
--> Inline styling takes first precedence followed by internal and external.

22.) Can several selectors with class names be grouped together?
--> Yes, you can group several selectors with class names.

23.) What happens if you open the external CSS file in a browser?
--> It will just open and display the contents of the css file as it is.

24.) How do you make a picture into a background image of a web page?
--> To set the background image of a webpage, use the CSS style. Under the CSS <style> tag, add the property background-image.

25.) What happens if the list-style-type property is used on a non-list element like a paragraph?
--> Property will be ignored and do not affect the paragraph.

26.) When is it appropriate to use frames?
--> Frames can make navigating a site much easier

27.) What happens if the number of values in the rows or cols attribute doesn’t add up to 100 percent?
--> The browser sizes the frames relative to the total sum of the values. If the cols attribute is set to 100%, 200% the browser displays two vertical frames with the second being twice as big as the first.

